s on using `Field.get` for static `VerificationType` fields. I’m wondering if using a fields list with `getDeclaredFields` in native will only return registered fields. It might only return fields related to access, especially if I emphasize static `VerificationType` fields. However, the code also checks `getType` and `getModifiers`, which can affect the population of the constants map. To narrow down metadata, it might be better to list fields explicitly, avoiding the broader scope of all declared fields.\\\\n\\\\n**Evaluating placeholder situation**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about a generic placeholder that seems to be a test file not properly mapped. It appears the existing placeholder isn't generated for the dynamic report, and only dynamic-access report classes might be generated one-to-one. I’m leaning towards deleting it, but I should verify this. I'm considering using \\\\\\\"git diff --cached,\\\\\\\" but maybe that's not necessary. I think I might just decide to finalize without taking that action.\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_06a1eb56240684a60169f40889cea0819783efe0158b6d84c4\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABp9AiZudHKjVR7wT9ge65Ja0fqkY70mBVLEIPiBtKH3_FT8klJJwZvyGw6Jxiz9b0wfL8pxkUXaJcWiUS5_9GgjdHdNu988_eqhBuFnIdyLVHfvSC2jwFgQFIcZWO0ycC0qcMi5ZjYhcgNs7x1_F0-uYTt1jm4bdPVzqGRi_pqfiN7mUnYIgwiY5ZA26pT51I92TNPTLzvbwvLszzsD0RN5V-hzKEgOuXwYC3GSFWsAv5pPk4AVwJDqnx0hs3GpczJ48glM_KWNtWtzIdWA8fb565n1EpdkaxwIZSzsnb3toKk6CIDJHEX7XvS0YCo5c_CNoYzf7LUXrNB395PKlOfLlEoqPKaLyjd70cjh8HeIWUgjHDNDmDXYZ03zNm3FJA3-YtUftKb9sMz41QBuBdH5QuBg1ofnW1LK4R3IAOK76Wq2-O3kz0FT1EFUlRn1H0olyrUfJQY6lPsAgXUWc3aURpHJUPHNC3vEbDEbKW3MOMg8weFI0zvTSvWujRJAbICIpfvKQ3MOpR16-465p0AkLtiZ20FImG2V8mlkLZijK4Ec65FS0k_Bkh_FKDdBfFoS56Sea_FrhjkNm3hf942B7-nr_lHy2a00mzObnT7GEWuQfT9d0eCHGhhO4q3XFm5R65LYiMd4MxlYfifznXxwnuBxO5IqIkw4yHb1nE_DeuTIyP_m9huTHoQhWfCYVonUx1L_au09nKq-YKdpWNXnC1Z59Rk_Si-0clSK2BZIt1ED9ryuDHCR